Leadership Tom Galle General Manager Chief Executive Officer Heather Donohue Chief Operating Officer Allison Roberts Chief Revenue Officer Tom Galle General Manager, Chief Executive Officer As Chief Executive Officer, Tom oversees national operations and customer service functions for TriZetto Provider Solutions, a Cognizant Company. Tom’s background in leading operations and service organizations spans more than 30 years. With extensive experience building organizational structures to drive efficiency and superior service, he brings years of success developing and executing operational strategies within start-up, growth and consolidation environments. Tom previously held leadership roles at Allianz Global Corporate & Specialty (AGCS), Utica National Insurance Group, MetLife and the Fireman’s Fund Insurance Company. Tom attended Lindenwood University and earned a bachelor’s degree in Business Administration. Michael Emerson Chief Information and Administrative Officer As Chief Information Officer, Mike leads TriZetto Provider Solutions, a Cognizant Company, in leveraging technology to transform, to drive growth and create a competitive advantage. His passion for innovation, combined with his business acumen and leadership capabilities, is key in helping TPS navigate the complex and rapidly changing digital landscape. As Chief Administrative Officer, Mike brings a wealth of experience and expertise in streamlining operations, and driving strategic initiatives across multiple functions within TPS. Mike excels in creating and nurturing cross-functional relationships, and his diverse background in international profit and non-profit sectors gives him a unique perspective in building efficient organizational structures while maximizing customer satisfaction. Prior to TriZetto Provider Solutions, he held global leadership positions in Allianz Global Corporate & Specialty (AGCS), worked as a Financial Consultant for the United Nations, and served as the Owner and CEO of a large medical supplies distributor in Istanbul, Turkey. Mike holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration from Bilkent University. Allison Roberts Chief Revenue Officer Allison Roberts brings over 25 years of healthcare industry experience to her role as Chief Revenue Officer at TriZetto Provider Solutions, a Cognizant Company, with expertise spanning strategy, operations, portfolio management and technology service delivery. In her position, she is responsible for customer success, business development and meeting global sales objectives through collaboration with payers, providers, channel partners, clients and prospective clients to increase efficiencies within revenue cycle processes. A results-oriented leader, she spearheads ideas and forms seamless partnerships with marketing and product teams to create creative solutions to solve diverse client needs. Her client-first approach is achieved by encouraging her associates to build long lasting relationships with clients to solve business issues so they can focus on providing quality care. Allison also serves as an executive lead for the TriZetto Provider Solutions Ambassador Team, an internal group of associates focused on building and executing the company’s Heart for Service initiative. Prior to TriZetto Provider Solutions, she worked at a major insurance company as well as an independent physician’s group. In her spare time, Allison stays busy watching her three daughters play soccer and is actively involved in her community through recycling and environmental conservation projects. She earned a bachelor’s degree in healthcare management from Southern Illinois University, Carbondale. Heather Donohue Chief Operating Officer Heather Donohue brings over 20 years of healthcare industry experience to her role as Chief Operating Officer of TriZetto Provider Solutions, a Cognizant Company. Heather plays an integral role as a TriZetto Provider Solutions Executive Leadership team member and is a strategic leader with a proven track record of cultivating innovation, driving organizational efficiencies, transforming and improving performance, enhancing client relations, and increasing associate satisfaction. In her role as Chief Operating Office, Heather oversees national operations, including client services, account management, payer management, technical operations, and all other aspects supporting the products and services of TriZetto Provider Solutions. When away from work, Heather enjoys spending time with her family, the beach, traveling, and experiencing new cultures

The TriZetto Provider Solutions Story We keep a pulse on your business so you can focus on providing care. At TriZetto Provider Solutions, we aim to simplify the business of healthcare. By combining intuitive products and customer-focused services with in-depth industry knowledge, we provide complete revenue cycle management services to empower our clients to succeed. Fueled by Cognizant, our collective expertise and global reach allows for endless possibilities to work with our clients to transform healthcare. Our Heart for Service We like to think that our products and services act as the heartbeat of our clients’ practices, and our company-wide promise to have a Heart for Service will serve as the underlying force that allows our clients’ businesses to thrive through dedicated customer service. We believe when you put heart into what you do, anything is possible. TriZetto Provider Solutions is looking toward the future and working to positively disrupt the healthcare industry. As we move forward, we believe our associates, initiatives and industry-leading products and services will allow us to provide the best service to our clients. Explore our Capabilities

Billing Services A consultative approach. Your clients have high expectations. Whether looking to build efficiencies or expand capabilities, we can help your organization unlock its potential. Through our Strategic Billing Company Program, we design a customized plan of the right products, services and subject matter experts that will help you meet deliverables quicker and exceed goals. Let us help you support every facet of your client’s revenue cycle by allowing your business to offer the best possible service. With our solutions, you can: Join a consultative partnership and receive tailored solutions Enhance your service portfolio Improve clean claim rates with the right tools Elevate patient satisfaction through price transparency Avoid credentialing, eligibility, coding and technical denials Decrease costs while increasing revenue U.S. physicians leave approximately $125 billion on the table each year due to poor billing practices
